cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper focuses on measuring social media activity of scientific literature, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data. This aligns with the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) which deals with the management, organization, and retrieval of digital information. Additionally, the use of altmetrics and big data in the study suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The study also involves analyzing correlations and associations between different factors, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). Lastly, the study involves analyzing scientific literature, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
